						<summary>

						<p>Stone water-cistern by the road-side.</p>						

						<p>1571 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This record dated, <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1493, Prajōtpatti Ve. śu. 5, Sunday,</hi> states that the water-trough was set up by Kuuṁñidēvarasa <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Doṁba-heggaḍe to secure merit. The details of date correspond to <hi rend="bold">1571 A.D., April 29,</hi> the month obviously being Vaiśākha.</p>						

						</summary>
